2.1.1. Continuum Theory Description of the Shock Wave Structure
The shock wave propagation was modelled using the one-dimensional Euler equations for
compressible flow [9,10], which were represented by the conservation of mass, momentum, and
energy, respectively, in the regions before and after the shock wave interface.
